@startuml end-to-end-settlement-flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Financial Message to On-Chain Settlement\nEnd-to-End Flow (with Idempotency)

actor "Financial System" as FS #LightBlue
box "AWS (Web2 Layer)" #E8F4FD
    participant "Ingestion API" as API
    participant "Normalizer" as NORM
    participant "KMS Signer" as KMS
    database "DynamoDB" as DDB
    database "S3" as S3
end box

box "Chainlink CRE (Web3 Orchestration)" #FFF3E0
    participant "CRE Workflow" as CRE
end box

box "Blockchain (Source of Truth)" #E8F5E9
    participant "KeyRegistry" as KEYS
    participant "SettlementConsumer" as SC
    participant "Token" as TOKEN
end box

== 1. Message Ingestion (AWS) ==
FS -> API : Send financial message\n(e.g., SWIFT MT103)
activate API
API -> S3 : Store raw message off-chain
API -> API : Compute messageDigest\n(keccak256 hash)
API --> FS : Acknowledge receipt
deactivate API

== 2. Normalization & Idempotency Check (AWS) ==
API -> NORM : Forward message + digest
activate NORM
NORM -> NORM : Extract semantic fields:\n• amount\n• parties\n• value time\n• reference
NORM -> NORM : Create Canonical Settlement Instruction (CSI)

note right of NORM #FFFACD
  **AWS Idempotency Key Derivation:**
  keccak256(
    "CSI_IDEMPOTENCY_V1" ||
    messageDigest ||
    asset || amount ||
    fromParty || toParty ||
    valueTime || intent ||
    chainId || referenceHash
  )
end note

NORM -> DDB : Check idempotency key exists?
alt Idempotency Key EXISTS (duplicate request)
    DDB --> NORM : Return existing instructionId
    NORM --> API : Return existing CSI\n(no duplicate created)
    API --> FS : 200 OK (existing instruction)
else Idempotency Key NOT FOUND (new request)
    DDB --> NORM : Key not found
    NORM -> NORM : Derive deterministic instructionId
    NORM -> DDB : Store idempotency mapping\n+ CSI (status: PENDING)
end
deactivate NORM

== 3. Institutional Signing (AWS) ==
NORM -> KMS : Request EIP-712 signature
activate KMS

note right of KMS #FFFACD
  **EIP-712 Domain:**
  name = "SettlementInstruction"
  version = "1"
  chainId = <target chain>
  verifyingContract = <SettlementConsumer>
end note

KMS -> KMS : Sign CSI with\ninstitutional key (HSM)
KMS --> NORM : Return signature (v, r, s)
deactivate KMS
NORM -> DDB : Store signed CSI\n(status: PENDING)

== 4. Workflow Execution (Chainlink CRE) ==
CRE -> API : GET /instructions/pending
activate CRE
API -> DDB : Query status=PENDING
DDB --> API : Return pending CSIs
API --> CRE : Return signed CSI batch

CRE -> CRE : Encode CSI + signature\ninto DON report
CRE -> SC : Submit via KeystoneForwarder\nonReport(report)
activate SC

== 5. On-Chain Settlement (Smart Contracts) ==
SC -> SC : Verify caller is KeystoneForwarder
SC -> KEYS : Verify signer is authorized
KEYS --> SC : Signer valid ✓

SC -> SC : Verify EIP-712 signature
SC -> SC : Check block.timestamp <= expiry
SC -> SC : Check chainId == block.chainid

note right of SC #FFE4E1
  **On-Chain Idempotency Check:**
  require(!executed[instructionId],
    "ALREADY_EXECUTED");
end note

SC -> SC : Check executed[instructionId] == false

alt instructionId ALREADY EXECUTED (replay attempt)
    SC --> CRE : Revert: "ALREADY_EXECUTED"
    CRE -> API : POST /instructions/{id}/status\n(status: FAILED, reason: duplicate)
    API -> DDB : Update status: FAILED
else instructionId NOT EXECUTED (valid)
    SC -> SC : executed[instructionId] = true

    alt intent == MINT_ONLY (Issuance)
        SC -> TOKEN : mint(toParty, amount)
        TOKEN --> SC : Mint complete
    else intent == BURN_AND_MINT (Reallocation)
        SC -> TOKEN : burn(fromParty, amount)
        TOKEN --> SC : Burn complete
        SC -> TOKEN : mint(toParty, amount)
        TOKEN --> SC : Mint complete
    else intent == BURN_ONLY (Redemption)
        SC -> TOKEN : burn(fromParty, amount)
        TOKEN --> SC : Burn complete
    end

    SC -> SC : Emit SettlementExecuted event
    SC --> CRE : Transaction confirmed (txHash)
    deactivate SC

    CRE -> API : POST /instructions/{id}/status\n(status: CONFIRMED, txHash)
    deactivate CRE
    API -> DDB : Update status: CONFIRMED\n+ txHash
end

== Idempotency Summary ==

note over FS, TOKEN
  **Two-Layer Idempotency Protection:**

  **Layer 1 - AWS (DynamoDB):**
  • Idempotency key computed from CSI content
  • Duplicate API calls return existing instruction
  • Enables safe retries on timeout/failure

  **Layer 2 - On-Chain (Solidity):**
  • mapping(bytes32 => bool) executed
  • Each instructionId settles exactly once
  • Protects against CRE retries or duplicate triggers

  **Result:** Safe end-to-end retries at every layer
end note

@enduml
